</ul>";}}s:10:"custom_nav";s:18:"Radiology Services";s:11:"description";s:161:"Pediatric radiology focuses on diagnosis of injuries and diseases in children ─ taking into account the dynamics of a growing body and exposure to radiation.";s:20:"one_sentence_summary";s:87:"Devoted to the diagnostic imaging and diagnosis of diseases and treatment for children.";s:9:"_template";s:16:"services/service";s:5:"_file";s:91:"/home/stpaulra/public_html/_content/03-services/02-radiology/09-pediatric-radiology/page.md";s:11:"_local_path";s:56:"/03-services/02-radiology/09-pediatric-radiology/page.md";s:10:"_order_key";s:2:"09";s:13:"datetimestamp";N;s:9:"datestamp";N;s:4:"date";N;s:4:"time";N;s:7:"numeric";s:2:"09";s:13:"last_modified";i:1464192394;s:10:"_is_hidden";b:0;s:9:"_is_draft";b:0;s:4:"slug";s:4:"page";s:7:"_folder";s:18:"services/radiology";s:9:"_basename";s:7:"page.md";s:9:"_filename";s:4:"page";s:9:"_is_entry";i:0;s:8:"_is_page";i:1;s:3:"url";s:39:"/services/radiology/pediatric-radiology";s:9:"permalink";s:69:"http://www.stpaulradiology.com/services/radiology/pediatric-radiology";}}s:22:"neuroradiology/page.md";a:5:{s:6:"folder";s:18:"services/radiology";s:4:"path";s:51:"/03-services/02-radiology/08-neuroradiology/page.md";s:4:"file";s:22:"neuroradiology/page.md";s:3:"url";s:34:"/services/radiology/neuroradiology";s:4:"data";a:27:{s:9:"_fieldset";s:7:"service";s:5:"title";s:14:"Neuroradiology";s:11:"img_primary";s:39:"/assets/img/services/Neuroradiology.jpg";s:8:"sections";a:2:{i:0;a:4:{s:4:"type";s:11:"set_section";s:13:"section_title";s:12:"General Info";s:11:"section_img";s:54:"/assets/img/services/Neuroradiology-20151019124138.jpg";s:15:"section_content";s:1057:"<h3>General Information About Neuroradiology</h3><p>Neuroradiology focuses on the central nervous system (brain and spinal cord) and peripheral nervous system (connecting the central nervous system to limbs and organs), the spine, and head and neck. Neuroradiologists provide primary imaging interpretation of magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) and computed tomography (CT) scans of the head, brain and spine, and perform some diagnostic and therapeutic procedures including pain management injections.</p><p>Similar to other branches of radiology, neuroradiology has both diagnostic and interventional aspects to the subspecialty and uses multiple imaging services for various indications and diagnosis. Examinations performed include both diagnostic MRI and CT along with therapeutic procedures such as pain management injections.</p><p><strong>Common Diseases:</strong></p><ul><li>Cerebrovascular Disease - stroke</li><li>Neoplastic Disease - brain tumor</li><li>Trauma - brain hemorrhage</li><li>Inflammatory/Infectious Disease - MS<span></span></li></ul>";}i:1;a:4:{s:4:"type";s:11:"set_section";s:13:"section_title";s:21:"Practicing Physicians";s:11:"section_img";s:51:"/assets/img/services/SPR Doctors-20151019124143.jpg";s:15:"section_content";s:2107:"<h3>Neuroradiology Physicians at St. Paul Radiology
